            <h2 id="section1">How we can help</h2>
            
            <p>We provide financial support for current and former ADF members for conditions accepted as related to your service.</p>
			<p>This may include payment for:</p>

			<ul>
			  <li>loss of function or lifestyle (permanent impairment)</li>
			  <li>loss of income (incapacity payments)</li>
			  <li>Special Rate Disability Payment (SRDP)</li>
			  <li>educational assistance for eligible dependants</li>
			</ul>
           
            <h2 id="section2">Types available</h2>

            <h3>Permanent impairment</h3>

				<p>If you have an accepted condition, you may be entitled to receive permanent impairment (PI) compensation from us if:</p>

				<ol>
				  <li>after treatment you still have an impairment</li>
				  <li>the impairment is likely to continue indefinitely</li>
				  <li>your condition has stabilised</li>
				</ol>

				<p>PI compensation is paid for both:</p>

				<ul>
				  <li>permanent physical and mental impairments</li>
				  <li>lifestyle restrictions resulting from your accepted conditions</li>
				</ul>

				<p>If you are entitled to receive PI compensation, you can choose to be paid:</p>

				<ul>
				  <li>a fortnightly periodic payment</li>
				  <li>a lump sum</li>
				  <li>a combination of part fortnightly periodic payment and part lump sum</li>
				</ul>

				<p><a href="https://www.dva.gov.au/factsheet-mrc07-permanent-impairment-compensation-payments">Discover more about permanent impairment.</a></p>

			<h3>Incapacity benefits</h3>

				<p>We may be able to pay you incapacity benefits if your condition caused an inability, or reduced ability, to work.</p>

				<p>This can include:</p>

				<ul>
				  <li>loss of income</li>
				  <li>loss of allowance while serving (for example, deployment allowance, seagoing allowance and district allowance)</li>
				  <li>delay in graduation</li>
				  <li>employment downgrade</li>
				  <li>loss of civilian employment</li>
				  <li>taking sick or unpaid leave in civilian employment</li>
				</ul>

				<p><a href="https://www.dva.gov.au/factsheet-mrc08-incapacity-work">Discover more about incapacity benefits.</a></p>

			<h3>Special Rate Disability Payment (SRDP)</h3>

				<p>If your capacity for work has been severely restricted because of conditions due to ADF service on or after 1 July 2004, you may be eligible for SRDP.</p>

				<p>SRDP is not automatically granted. If you are eligible, you can choose to start receiving SRDP or continue receiving incapacity benefits.</p>

				<p><a href="https://www.dva.gov.au/factsheet-mrc09-special-rate-disability-pension-srdp">Discover more about Special Rate Disability Payments.</a></p>

			<h3>Education schemes</h3>

				<p>Education schemes help students achieve their potential in full-time education or career training.</p>

				<p>We can assist certain dependants of eligible ADF members, and former members, with accepted conditions.</p>

				<p>Students may be eligible for the following benefits under the education schemes:</p>

				<ul>
				  <li>education allowance</li>
				  <li>special assistance</li>
				  <li>fares allowance</li>
				  <li>rent assistance</li>
				  <li>additional tuition</li>
				  <li>guidance and counselling</li>
				  <li>tertiary Student Start-up and Relocation Scholarships</li>
				  <li>Energy Supplement payments</li>
				  <li>Income Support Bonus payments</li>
				</ul>

				<p><a href="https://www.dva.gov.au/factsheet-mrc47-education-schemes">Discover more about education schemes.</a></p>
             
